The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Ex-MP son found dead in US

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Lucknow, Nov. 19: The son of former MP and Muslim scholar Syed Shahabuddin was found dead on the Columbia University campus in New York on Thursday evening.

 At 43, Nayyar Pervez was one of the youngest professors at the university. He is survived by wife Soofia and children, Zohra, 9, and Zain, 5.

 Pervezs family here was informed of his death this morning and Shahabuddin left soon after for the US. 

 Sources in his family said Pervez had last called his wife on Wednesday evening. He did not return home that night.

 The cause of Pervezs death is undetermined, the sources said, adding that investigating agencies in the US are suspecting foul play. An autopsy is being done to confirm the nature of the death.

 A graduate from IIT Delhi and Stanford University, Pervez joined Columbia University in 1995. The university awarded him the 2004 Great Teacher Certificate.

 Pervezs body will be flown to India on Monday. 




